The '''1991 Gator Bowl''' was a [[bowl game|postseason]] [[college football]] match between [[Oklahoma Sooners football|Oklahoma Sooners]] and the [[Virginia Cavaliers football|Virginia Cavaliers]] at the [[Gator Bowl Stadium]] in [[Jacksonville, Florida]]. The University of Oklahoma represented the [[Big Eight Conference]] and Virginia represented the [[Atlantic Coast Conference]] (ACC) in the competition. The game was the final competition of the [[1991 NCAA Division I-A football season|1991 football season]] for each team and resulted in a 48â14 Oklahoma victory, even though [[spread betting|spread bettors]] favored Virginia to win by 1.5 points.<ref name="ref1"/>
